race.comment: INQUISITOR (3) won comfortably over 1415m at Ballina two runs ago then dropped backed to 1300m at Lismore last time and was strong late, beaten a length in a Class 2. Finds an easier race today so despite the big weight he looks the testing material. IN THE FINE PRINT (2) continued his excellent form of late when he bolted in over the mile at Coffs Harbour three weeks ago. A wide alley doesn't help but he is going too well to rule out. The lightly raced SPICY WINGS (6) needs luck from the draw but is progressing well and looks up to this. JUSTAFEVER (11) shoots for the hat trick and is unbeaten at the distance. Must respect winning form.
